xample analyses to show how the orchard is created in narrative as a consistent, three-dimensional space of action and imagination and how this develops, semanticizes, and functionalizes its conflict potential for the narrative.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aLiterature, MedievalxHistory and criticism. 0aOrchards. 4aErzählforschung. 4aHöfischer Roman. 4aIntimität. 4aKinästhetik. 4aPerformativität. 4aRaum. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Medieval.2bisacsh  aChivalric romance.  aintimacy.  akinesthetics.  anarrative studies.  aperformativity.  aspace.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2023 Part 1z978311117578208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary Studies 2023z9783111318264oZDB-23-DSP0 cEPUBz97831107954930 cprintz978311079538740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311079545540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110795455423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110795455/original  a978-3-11-117578-2  DG Plus DeG Package 2023 Part 1b2023  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2023  aZDB-23-DSPb2023